(3486, 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/beef_and_aubergine_46108\n', 'https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/food/ic/food_16x9_832/recipes/beef_and_aubergine_46108_16x9.jpg\n', 'Beef and aubergine fatteh \n', ' This is a subtly textured, richly flavoured arrangement of toasted pieces of flatbread topped with meaty aubergine and beef, a garlicky tahini-yoghurt sauce, red pepper flakes, pomegranate seeds, toasted pine nuts and fresh shredded mint. Is it too terrible to say that I think of it as Middle-Eastern nachos? \n', 30, 90, 4, 17),
(3487, 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/calabrian_pork_ribs_75821\n', 'https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/food/ic/food_16x9_832/recipes/calabrian_pork_ribs_75821_16x9.jpg\n', 'Calabrian pork ribs\n', ' This flavoursome pork rib roast is cut from pork belly still on the bone. Perfect for marinating and then cooking low and slow before a quick grill or go on the barbecue.\n', 30, 120, 4, 13),
(3488, 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/fried_red_mullet_with_82300\n', 'https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/food/ic/food_16x9_832/recipes/fried_red_mullet_with_82300_16x9.jpg\n', 'Fried red mullet with oranges and capers\n', ' The red mullet off Monemvasia are supposedly the best in the Aegean. A net full of them, red yes, but pink too with flashes of yellow as the sun rose on a still dark blue sea is a lovely recollection, and fried for breakfast later they were quite memorable. A month later though, I saw three autumn mullet in our fish shop and I cooked them simply with a dusting of semolina. I used to think the Mediterranean mullet were better than ours, but now I know the ones that come to Cornwall in autumn are pretty hard to beat.\n', 30, 30, 4, 12),
(3489, 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/grilledlambcutletsfi_70345\n', 'https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/832xn/p027vzb8.jpg\n', 'Grilled lamb cutlets filled with parma ham and herbs\n', ' None\n', 90, 10, 4, 11),
(3490, 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/pear_and_raspberry_15343\n', 'https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/images/ic/832xn/p07f3ykj.jpg\n', 'Pear and raspberry frangipane tart\n', ' You could buy raspberry jam to cheat this tart a little, but it’s definitely worth making the pastry from scratch.\n', 90, 120, 1, 20),
