(3509, 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/find-the-filling_buns_43954\n', 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/friedfishinoatmealwi_91975\n', 'https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/poppy_seed_cake_with_92678\n', ' https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/pennewithpancettaand_88250\n https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/sultana_scones_with_98294\n https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/roughpuffpastry_89772\n https://www.bbc.co.uk/food/recipes/chocolate_volcanoes_37330\n https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/food/ic/food_16x9_832/recipes/chocolate_volcanoes_37330_16x9.jpg\n Chocolate volcanoes\n Paul\'s version of the classic chocolate fondant is all about timing. Don’t let the puddings bake to the point that their surface begins to crack, as this means the centres are starting to cook. \n', 120, 30, 6, 8),
